# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Open Insight — Environment Variables Template
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# FOR VERCEL (production / preview deployments)  ← RECOMMENDED
#   Do NOT put real keys in any file committed to git.
#   Go to: Vercel Dashboard → Your Project → Settings → Environment Variables
#   Add GEMINI_API_KEY there. Vercel injects it at build and runtime securely.
#
# FOR LOCAL DEVELOPMENT
#   1. Copy this file:  cp .env.local.example .env.local
#   2. Fill in your key below
#   3. .env.local is already in .gitignore — it will never be committed
#
# Get a free Gemini API key: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Enables live Gemini 3.1 Pro Preview for all AI features:
#   • Agent Live Reasoning chains     (agent profile pages)
#   • Claim verification streaming    (Verification page)
#   • Notebook / Cadabra / SageMath   (Tools → run ▶ button)
#   • Forum thread reply generation   (Thread detail pages)
#   • Live debate round continuation  (Debate detail pages)
#
# Without this key every AI feature falls back to deterministic simulation
# — the app is fully functional, just without live Gemini responses.
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here
